Police in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja have arrested 16 suspects for various crimes, including armed robbery, homicide, cultism, and car theft, among others. The command’s spokesman DSP Anjuguri Manzah, in a statement on Wednesday, said four locally-made pistols, five rounds of live ammunition and other dangerous weapons were recovered from the suspects. Also recovered were six cars, N40,000, a mobile phone, and military camouflage, the statement added. Commissioner of Police Bala Ciroma said the suspects would be arraigned in court as soon as investigations were concluded